name: Cafe Tato since 1913 (Patto)

reviews.review_text:
Such an iconic spot to savour some delicious Goan breakfast. We tried the sukhi bhaaji, tomato bhaaji and mushroom bhaaji along with fresh pooris and pav. All the dishes were simple yet packed with big flavours. We also tried the mirchi pakoda which was just too yum!!

This spot is old school and no nonsense - Small menu, delicious food and affordable prices

While on tour of Goa, we visited this place twice. It's a very good place for vegetarians. All items were good in taste and service was also really good. It's a must visit place.
Puri, Buns, Kaju bhaji, sukhi bhaji, tomato-onion bhaji, lime water, tea all were really good in taste.

Lived up to our expectations!!!
Authentic Goan Breakfast place!
Service is amazing!
Clean!
We tried their famous sukhi bhaaji with puri
Also the mirchi bajji
The star for me was the raagi pudding with jaggery it's a must try!!!!

description:
**Café Tato Since 1913: A Culinary Gem in Goa**

Nestled in the vibrant heart of Goa, Café Tato since 1913 has been a beloved breakfast destination for locals and tourists alike, boasting an impressive rating of 4.4 stars from 778 reviews. This iconic eatery is renowned for its authentic Goan cuisine, with tags such as “Goan” (37 mentions), “veg food” (18 mentions), “buns” (17 mentions), and “puri bhaji” (15 mentions) illuminating its standout offerings. 

**Ambiance & Design:**
Walking into Café Tato, you are greeted by a charming no-frills atmosphere that pays homage to its long-standing heritage. The décor reflects a traditional Goan feel, characterized by simple furnishings that provide a cozy yet unpretentious dining experience. The soft yellow and cream tones of the walls, alongside rustic wooden tables, create a warm, inviting space perfect for a leisurely breakfast. Reviewers have noted the cleanliness of the establishment, which compliments its age-old charm. The ambient noise is characterized by the chatter of satisfied customers, making it a bustling spot for breakfast lovers.

**Menu & Culinary Experience:**
Café Tato’s menu beautifully encapsulates the essence of Goan breakfast fare, primarily focused on vegetarian dishes. Patrons rave about the “sukhi bhaaji,” a dry vegetable curry that pairs wonderfully with fresh, fluffy puris, making it a beloved staple. The menu also features other comforting options like the “kaju bhaji” and “mirchi pakoda,” both of which have garnered glowing reviews. One standout that should not be missed is the “raagi pudding with jaggery,” praised as a delightful and must-try treat. Each dish is described as simple yet bursting with flavor, showcasing the ability of the café to turn humble ingredients into satisfying meals. The presentations are unpretentious but inviting, served on classic dishware that adds to the homely feel.

**Customer Experience & Service:**
The service at Café Tato has been consistently described as friendly and efficient, with attentive staff ready to cater to diners’ needs. Many customers appreciate the no-nonsense attitude of the café, which focuses on delivering quality food without unnecessary embellishments. Reviews confirm that this eatery is particularly vegetarian-friendly, making it a great choice for those looking to indulge without compromising their dietary preferences. Walk-ins are welcome, providing flexibility for spontaneous breakfast outings.

**Popularity & Reviews:**
Café Tato has grown into a beloved institution over its century-long history, enjoying buzz not just from diners but also on social media platforms. Its authentic approach to Goan cuisine has made it a must-visit spot for anyone exploring the region, with various culinary enthusiasts and tourists highlighting it as a key part of their Goan experience. The favorable reviews echo the sentiment that Café Tato represents the heart of Goan breakfast culture.

**Utilizing Visual Content:**
Customer-provided photos beautifully encapsulate the vibrant dishes served at Café Tato, showcasing colorful plates of bhaaji alongside freshly made puris and buns. These images not only illustrate the simple, homey presentation but also capture the lively atmosphere of the café, filled with smiling diners enjoying their meals. The photos reflect a place that feels both welcoming and steeped in culinary tradition.

In summary, Café Tato since 1913 is more than just a restaurant; it’s a culinary landmark in Goa, offering a delightful journey through the flavors of traditional Goan breakfast. Whether you're a local or a visitor, this café promises a satisfying experience that celebrates the region’s rich gastronomic heritage. Enjoy the simplicity, embrace the flavors, and immerse yourself in a slice of Goan culture at this iconic breakfast spot.
